<blockquote><p>
I can never get people to understand that poetry is the expression of <em>excited passion</em>, and that there is no such thing as a life of passion any more than a continuous earthquake, or an eternal fever. Besides, who would ever <em>shave</em> themselves in such a state?
</p></blockquote>
<p>&#8212; Lord Byron, <a href="https://books.google.com/books?id=bZZQ3Q2xocYC&#038;pg=PA474">letter</a> to Thomas Moore, July 5, 1821</p>
